Description: Six joining body sherds of Attic black-glazed pottery skyphos; vertical rim; glazed black on interior and exterior.
Curator's comments: 1965,0930.868b-c almost certainly belong to the same skyphos, but do not join. 'CEM' with arrow scratched on interior of two of the joining sherds.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1259)
